Some of the questions were incomplete. For example, the second question asked for opinion distribution on how "following policies" would affect economic inequality and illegal immigration, but there were no policies listed. I don't know if this was intentional or not.

It was an interesting survey.
none

The 2nd question in this survey made absolutely no sense to me, because I think it might have been incomplete. 

It reads something to the effect of "how much would these policy changes impact racism" but never lists what policy changes it's referring to. 

I have no idea about how my response should be or what my opinion is because I did not see any policy changes listed to have an opinion about. 

I based my answer on the fact that s lot of other people wouldn't read the question and just answer based on how they "feel" about the topic rather than what the content actually was.

It would help if the answer key was written out next to each one in each segment.  For example, under "how many...women...", have "refused" next to the letter "D" (or whatever), under "how many...men", have "refused" next to the letter "D", etc.  That would help so that I didn't need to keep going back to the top for the answer key.  

I went over time because I'm a slow reader and I was really thinking about the questions and deciding.  I hope I'll still be paid as expected.  Interesting survey.  Really gets me thinking about things.
no comments

It would be helpful to add in what each letter choice stands for throughout the question.  I had to scroll back multiple times for each question to refresh my memory.  Some people might just guess incorrectly because it requires extra effort to scroll back repeatedly.
It would be easier to be able to see what the options mean all the way down the page instead of having to scroll back up.  Just a thought...
